6. (18)

The Buddhas designated a self;
And taught there is no self;
They also taught that
There is neither self nor selflessness.

8. (18)

Everything is real; and everything is not real;
Both real and unreal;
Neither unreal nor real.
That is the Lord Buddha's teaching.
7

17. (24)
Results and causes;
Agents, instruments and actions;
Arising and ceasing;
As well as the results would be undermined.

37. (24)
To undermine emptiness means
That there is no action;
That there can be action without effort;
And that there can be an agent who performs no
action.

39. (24)
If they were not empty,
Then there would be no attainment of the unattained;
Nor the act of ending suffering;
Nor the elimination of karma and all the afflictions.
